data.name: AlertBox5.Text
data.value: Some applications and Control Panel applets use the 'MS Shell Dlg' font. There is a registry trick that substitutes these fonts with others. They are originally replaced by 'Microsoft Sans Serif' and 'Tahoma'.

data.name: AlertBox7.Text
data.value: To return to the default settings in Windows 7 and 8.1, click on the 'Undo' buttons above, log off, and then log back in to your Windows account. Afterward, go back to WinPaletter, reload the 'Default Windows' settings from the button above, apply the changes, and log off again.

data.name: tips_box.Text
data.value: - Drag and drop sizing boxes on preview windows to change element sizes and values. - A left-click with dragging on the window will change the title bar and border size, while a right-click will change the padding border width. - Clicking on an item will change its font.

data.name: alertBox1.Text
data.value: Title bar fonts are not changeable in Windows 11 for an unknown reason (or related to visual styles). They will remain in 'Segoe UI' but with different sizes. You can change the title bar font size and other sizes values.
